    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-05-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="411"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d411">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Pratt</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-05-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 27, 1890</date>. (Received July
                        2.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 458.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report, regarding the
                    attempted assassination of Mrs. Wright, treated of in my dispatches numbered 456
                    and 457 of the 24th and 27th instant, respectively, that I am now awaiting an
                    official account of the said incident from Col. C. E. Stewart, the English
                    consul-general at Tabreez, in whose district the crime was committed.</p>
                <p>American interests being under the protection of the British consul in the said
                    district, the British minister here, Sir Henry Drummond Wolff, has very kindly
                    assented to my request to allow Colonel Stewart to officially represent me in
                    the prosecution of the case in question.</p>
                <p>This course, which I trust will meet with your approval, I thought the safest to
                    adopt in view of the danger of the prisoner’s escaping en route had I insisted
                    upon his being transported hither for trial.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. Spencer Pratt.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
